<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="327" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,909,1801]" pageId="11" pageNumber="327">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1668,1693]" pageId="11" pageNumber="327">Comments.</emphasis>
This species is distinguished by its coloration, with yellow head, brown antenna with white annulus at the apex, mesosoma dark brown with lighter propodeum and the first tergum of metasoma light brown and granulose.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1437,1776,1801]" pageId="11" pageNumber="327" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,909,1801]" box="[199,1437,1776,1801]" pageId="11" pageNumber="327">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1776,1801]" pageId="11" pageNumber="327">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named in honour of Daniela C. de Melo who helped in the conclusion of this work.
</paragraph>
